## Ingredients

- [ ] 2 Tbsps extra-virgin olive oil
- [ ] 1 small yellow onion, chopped
- [ ] 1 Tbsp grated fresh ginger
- [ ] 4 garlic cloves, minced
- [ ] 2 Tbsps yellow curry powder
- [ ] 1/2 tsp ground cinnamon
- [ ] 4 cups vegetable or chicken stock
- [ ] 2 (13.5-ounce) cans full-fat coconut milk, shaken
- [ ] 1.5 pounds sweet potato, peeled and cut into 1-inch pieces
- [ ] 1.5 cups brown lentils
- [ ] 1.5 tsp sea salt, plus more to taste
- [ ] 4 cups packed stemmed and roughly torn curly kale

## Recipe

1. Heat olive oil in large stockpot over medium heat. Add onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Add ginger and garlic, cook 1-2 minutes until fragrant. Stir in curry powder and cinnamon.
1. Pour in stock and coconut milk. Stir in sweet potatoes, lentils, and salt. Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer covered, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes until vegetables and lentils are tender. Uncover, add kale, and cook 3-5 minutes until wilted.
1. Ladle into bowls and serve warm.

## Notes

- Vegan, gluten-free, and dairy-free
- Brown lentils recommended for texture; French, black, or green lentils work as alternatives
- Freezes well for meal prep
- Serves 8, prep time 15 minutes, cook time 30 minutes
